    generate_miss: Generate missing values with different mechanisms

    generate_miss.Rd

    generate_miss function generates missing values in a complete dataframe with the chosen mechanism and the chosen proportion of missingness.

    generate_miss(df, miss_perc, mechanism = "MCAR", mar2.col.ctrl = 1)

    Arguments

    df

    Complete dataframe.

    miss_perc

    Desired percentage of missing values. Note that all the mechanisms could only approach this proportion. The real proportion of missingness will be returned with the incomplete dataframe. When the number of columns is small, some mechanisms could be incompatible with large missing percentage.

    mechanism

    Desired missing mechanism.

    • MCAR generates missing values by missing completely at random mechanism with Bernouilli distribution.

    • MAR1 generates missing values by missing at random mechanism with logistic regression on the observed data.

    • MAR2 generates missing values by missing at random mechanism with censoring algorithm. The missingness in every other column depends on the quantile of one specified complete column mar2.col.ctrl. For example, on row i, Y2[i] will be removed if Y1[i]<q(30%) of Y1.

    • MAR3 generates missing values by missing at random mechanism with monotone censoring mechanism. The missingness in every column depends on the quantile of the observed data of the column before. For example, on row i, Y2[i],Y3[i],...,Yn[i] will be removed if Y1[i]<q(30%) of Y1. And then on row s, Y3[s],...,Yn[s] will be removed if Y2[s]<q(30%) of observed Y2 (Those who are not removed in step 1). If MAR3 is chosen, it is better to rearrange df so the numerical columns are placed before the categorical ones.

    • MNAR1 generates missing values by missing not at random mechanism with logistic regression on the observed and missing part of data.

    • MNAR2 generates missing values by missing not at random mechanism with censoring mechanism. For example, for each column j, on row i, Yj[i] will be removed if Yj[i]<q(30%) of Yj.

    mar2.col.ctrl

    Control column in mechanism MAR2

    Value

    X.incomp Generated incomplete dataframe. R.mask Mask of missingness. R[2,3]=1 means that df[2,3] is missing. real_miss_perc Real proportion of missingness.

    References

    • https://rmisstastic.netlify.app/how-to/generate/misssimul

    • https://cran.r-project.org/package=missMethods/vignettes/Generating-missing-values.html

    • Santos, M. S., R. C. Pereira, A. F. Costa, J. P. Soares, J. Santos, and P. H. Abreu. 2019. Generating Synthetic Missing Data: A Review by Missing Mechanism. IEEE Access 7: 11651–67. doi: 10.1109/ACCESS.2019.2891360 .

    Examples

    n <- 10000
mu.X <- c(1, 2, 3)
Sigma.X <- matrix(c(9, 3, 2, 3, 4, 0, 2, 0, 1), nrow = 3)
X.complete.cont <- MASS::mvrnorm(n, mu.X, Sigma.X)
rs <- generate_miss(X.complete.cont, 0.5, mechanism = "MNAR2")
rs$X.incomp
